In dorsal view, the vertebra displays a wide zygosphene. The cranial margin of the zygosphene is somewhat convex and possesses distinct lateral lobes (BSPG 1997 XIII 519), or is concave with a wide median notch (
Fig. 7A
). Prezygapophyseal articular facets are broadly oval. Prezygapophyseal processes are short (less than ½ of the prezygapophyseal facets length) with a pointed tip.
